hopobject.body: What's the interest rate on this account? enferm medical Typically, high schools rely on seniors' exit interviews to gather information about which students transition to college after graduating, and what types of colleges they attend, Cook said. But sometimes, what students say they intend to do in those interviews does not line up with reality, due to a phenomenon known as the "summer melt." Under this scenario, many low-income high school graduates reconsider where, and even whether, to attend college in the months following graduation.
